# README

## 1.) Documentation

* please run docs/index.html

## 2.) Server

* sudo apt-get install nodejs npm grunt

### run:

* ./dev-server.js

* navigate to the browser on page:

* http://localhost:8001/

### 3.) Building

* grunt dist

* navigate to dist/ folder

# Application workflow

## 1.)

* create a module: testApp = onix.module("testApp", []);

* you can change application config: testApp.config(function(config) { ... config ... });

* entry point: testApp.run(); after execution of this function application starts $route

* in run function you can define $route pages with their controller functions

## 2.)

* controller entry function is _init() - runs from $route

* after this is functions, _afterInit() is executed - you can over ride it

## 3.)

* directive entry function is init() - you have to run this function manually

* init() function needs _create() to be filled with DOM root element

* after init(), setup() is need to bind all javascript to the view in directive

* activate(), deactivate() are supported functions - runs them manually

